---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<main class="content">
		<header class="hero">
			<div class="hero-grid">
				<div class="hero-text">
					<p class="kicker">Industrial Theology for People Under Pressure</p>
					<h1>Matter Precedes Hierarchy.</h1>
					<p class="lede">Materialist Christianity is not a spiritual retreat. It is a structural manual for those who deal in reality. Secure the master specification by Ezra Byrd below.</p>
					<div class="cta-row">
						<a class="btn primary highlight" href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FMN9T933" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SECURE THE MANUAL (AMAZON)</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="mockup-container">
					<img src="/book-cover.png" alt="Materialist Christianity Manual by Ezra Byrd" class="mockup-img" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</header>

		<section class="panel master-spec">
			<h2 class="section-label">The Core Schematic</h2>
			<h3>Faith as a Living Foundation</h3>
			<p>Modern religion has drifted into the clouds. We pull it back to the dirt. This text provides the complete mechanical framework for faith in an era of collapsing systems.</p>
			
			<div class="what-is-grid">
				<div class="concept-card">
					<h3>1. The 5 Rules</h3>
					<p>Non-negotiable structural constraints for human coordination.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="concept-card">
					<h3>2. Mechanical Morality</h3>
					<p>Why ethical behavior is a requirement of physics, not just social pressure.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="concept-card">
					<h3>3. Industrial Grace</h3>
					<p>How to maintain the machine when it begins to seize.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
